Shui Pin (constituency) - Wikipedia Shui Pin (constituency)From Wikipedia, the free encyclopediaJump to navigationJump to searchShui PinElected Constituencyfor the Yuen Long District CouncilBoundary of Shui Pin in Yuen Long DistrictDistrictYuen LongLegislative Council constituencyNew Territories North WestPopulation18,727 (2019)[1]Electorate10,019 (2019)[2]Current constituencyCreated1994Number of membersOneMember(s)VacantShui Pin (Chinese: 水邊) is one of the 39 constituencies in the Yuen Long District of Hong Kong.The constituency returns one district councillor to the Yuen Long District Council, with an election every four years. Shui Pin constituency is loosely based on Covent Garden, Emerald Green, Greenery Place, Park Royale, Parkside Villa, Scenic Gardens, Shui Pin Wai Estate, Springdale Villas and Villa Art Deco in Yuen Long with an estimated population of 18,727.[3]Contents1 Councillors represented2 Election results2.1 2010s3 ReferencesCouncillors represented[edit]ElectionMemberParty1991Cheung Yin-tungUnited Democrats1994Democratic1994Wong Kin-wingNonpartisan2007Yuen Man-yeeLiberal2008Nonpartisan2019Lai Kwok-wing→VacantTCHDNTW→NonpartisanElection results[edit]2010s[edit]Yuen Long District Council Election, 2019: Shui PinPartyCandidateVotes%±%Team Chu (PfD)Lai Kwok-wing3,79951.68IndependentYuen Man-yee3,46647.15NonpartisanIvaline Poon Sin-man861.17Majority3334.53Turnout7,38073.70Team Chu gain from IndependentSwingReferences[edit]^ "Recommended District Council Constituency Areas" (PDF). Electoral Affairs Commission.^ "Age and Sex profile of registered electors by 452 District Council Constituency Areas in 2019" (PDF). Registration and Electoral Office.^ "2015 District Councils Election - Summary of the District Council Constituency Areas". Hong Kong Government.vteYuen Long District Council (41)Democratic (7)Ching KingKingswood SouthNam PingPek LongShui OiYiu YauYuen Long Tung TauTSWC (4)Fu YanKingswood NorthShui WahTin ShingAction 18 (2)Shap Pat Heung CentralSh